      "`s {u, v} = {s u, s v}`.\n\nBut perhaps even easier: note that each edge in `q.2.edges` is `s e` for some `e ∈ p.2.edges`, and that this process is invertible, because the permutation is bijective. \n\nBut actually, perhaps we can directly use that `(permMap Walk n s p.2).edges = p.2.edges.image s`.\n\n#### Formal Proof Sketch\n\n1. Show that `(permMapWalk n s p).edges = p.edges.image s`, for any `p` (the proof will be by induction on `p`). \n   - For the base case `p = nil`, both sides are empty.\n   - For the cons case, the edges are updated by adding a new edge, and `s` distributes over the union.\n   - For the loop case, the edges remain the same (but actually loop case is not in the original proof).\n2. Then, deduce that the cardinality of `(permMapWalk n s p).edges` is equal to the cardinality of `p.edges` because `s` is injective.\n   - Use `Finset.card_image_of_injective`.\n\nBut the induction is already complex because of the different cases of `LoopWalk`. \n\nAlternatively, since the problem is only posed for closed loop walks in `K n`, and `K n` is a complete graph, perhaps we can do something simpler. \n\nBut perhaps it's better to follow the actual proof:\n\n**Lemma:**\n`(permMapWalk n s p).edges = p.edges.image s` for any `p`.\n\n**Proof sketch:**\nBy induction on `p`:\n- For `nil`, both sides are empty.\n- For `cons h p`, we have:\n  - `(permMapWalk n s (cons h p)).edges = (permMapWalk n s p).edges ∪ {s (edge of h)}`.\n  - `(cons h p).edges = p.edges ∪ {edge of h}`.\n  - So `(permMapWalk n s (cons h p)).edges = (p.edges.image s) ∪ {s (edge of h)} = ((p.edges ∪ {edge of h}).image s)`\n- For `loop p`, we have:\n  - `(permMapWalk n s (loop p)).edges = (permMapWalk n s p).edges = p.edges.image s`.\n  - `(loop p).edges = p.edges`.\n  - So the equality holds as `p.edges.image s = p.edges.image s`.\n\nBut in Lean, the actual definition of `edges` in `LoopWalk` is `(dart.map (fun (u, v) ↦ ({u, v} : Sym2 V))).toFinset`.\n\n**Actually, no:** `edges` is a coercion to `Finset (Sym2 V)`, which is `(dart.map (fun (u, v) ↦ ({u, v} : Sym2 V))).toFinset`. \n\nThen, for `permMapWalk n s p`, the `dart` is `p.dart.map (fun (u, v) ↦ (s u, s v))`. So `(permMapWalk n s p).edges = ( p.dart.map (fun (u, v) ↦ (s u, s v)) ).map (fun (u, v) ↦ ({u, v} : Sym2 V)) ).toFinset`.\n\nBut we can prove that `( p.dart.map (fun (u, v) ↦ (s u, s v)) ).map (fun (u, v) ↦ ({u, v} : Sym2 V)) = p.dart.map (fun (u, v) ↦ s ({u, v} : Sym2 V))`.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps we can prove that `(permMapWalk n s p).edges = p.edges.image (fun e ↦ s e)` by induction. \n\nBut perhaps we should use the fact that for a complete graph, the number of edges in any walk is equal to the number of darts divided by",
      "\n  obtain ⟨ s, hs ⟩ := heq;\n  rw [hs];\n  -- Since these two sets are equal, their cardinalities are equal.\n  have h_card_eq : (p.snd.edgeSet) = (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet.image s := by\n    -- For looped walks over the complete graph, the surjection property ensures we get 1-to-1 correspondence\n    have h1 : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p).edges = p.edges.map (Equiv(α := Edge (K n)) (β := Edge (K n)) (f := fun e : Edge (K n) => (s e.1, s e.2)) (g := fun e : Edge (K n) => (s.symm e.1, s.symm e.2)) (left_inv := by {\n      intro ⟨a, b|⟩\n      <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n      <;> congr <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n    }) (right_inv := by {\n      intro ⟨a, b|⟩\n      <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n      <;> congr <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n    }) (bijective := ⟨fun _ _ h => by {\n      simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]\n      <;> aesop\n    }, fun y => ⟨(s.symm y.1, s.symm y.2), by {\n      simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]\n      <;> aesop\n    }⟩⟩)) := by\n      intro u v p\n      induction' p with u v w h p ih\n      · rfl\n      · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.cons, Equiv.map_right]\n        <;>\n        dsimp_all [Equiv.map_right] <;>\n        simp_all [List.map]\n        <;>\n        try {\n          aesop\n        }\n        <;>\n        try {\n          simp_all [Sym2.mk.injEq] <;>\n          (try contradiction) <;>\n          (try simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n        }\n      · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.loop, Equiv.map_right]\n        <;>\n        dsimp_all [Equiv.map_right] <;>\n        simp_all [List.map]\n        <;>\n        try {\n          aesop\n        }\n        <;>\n        try {\n          simp_all [Sym2.mk.injEq] <;>\n          (try contradiction) <;>\n          (try simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n        }\n    have h2 : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset = ((p.snd.edges).map (Equiv(α := Edge (K n)) (β := Edge (K n)) (f := fun e : Edge (K n) => (s e.1, s e.2)) (g := fun e : Edge (K n) => (s.symm e.1, s.symm e.2)) (left_inv := by {\n      intro ⟨a, b|⟩\n      <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n      <;> congr <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n    }) (right_inv := by {\n      intro ⟨a, b|⟩\n      <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n      <;> congr <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n    }) (bijective := ⟨fun _ _ h => by {\n      simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]\n      <;> aesop\n    }, fun y => ⟨(s.symm y.1, s.symm y.2), by {\n      simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]\n      <;> aesop\n    }⟩⟩)).toFinset := by\n      rw [h1]\n      <;>\n      simp [List.toFinset_map]\n    have h3 : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset = (p.snd.edges.toFinset.image (fun e : Edge (K n) => (s e.1, s e.2))) := by\n      rw [h2]\n      <;>\n      simp [List.toFinset_map, Finset.image]\n      <;>\n      aesop\n    have h4 : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet.toFinset = (p.snd.edges.toFinset.image (fun e : Edge (K n) => (s e.1, s e.2))) := by\n      simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet] at *\n      <;>\n      simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, List.toFinset_map, Finset.image]\n      <;>\n      aesop\n    have h5 : (p.snd.edgeSet).toFinset = (p.snd.edges.toFinset.image (fun e : Edge (K n) => (s.symm e.1, s.symm e.2))) := by\n      simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet] at *\n      <;>\n      simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, List.toFinset_map, Finset.image]\n      <;>\n      aesop\n    have h6 : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet.toFinset = (p.snd.edgeSet).toFinset.image (fun e : Edge (K n) => (s e.1, s e.2)) := by\n      rw [h4]\n      <;>\n      (simp_all [Finset.image_image, Function.LeftInverse]\n        <;>\n        aesop)\n      <;>\n      (try {\n        have h7 : (fun e : Edge (K n) => (s.symm e.1, s.symm e.2)) = (Equiv(α := Edge (K n)) (β := Edge (K n)) (f := fun e : Edge (K n) => (s.symm e.1, s.symm e.2)) (g := fun e : Edge (K n) => (s e.1, s e.2)) (left_inv := by {\n          intro ⟨a, b|⟩\n          <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n          <;> congr <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n        }) (right_inv := by {\n          intro ⟨a, b|⟩\n          <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n          <;> congr <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n        }) (bijective := ⟨fun _ _ h => by {\n          simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]\n          <;> aesop\n        }, fun y => ⟨(s.symm y.1, s.symm y.2), by {\n          simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]\n          <;> aesop\n        }⟩⟩)).toFun := by\n          ext ⟨x, y⟩\n          <;> simp [Equiv.Perm.symm_apply_apply]\n          <;> aesop\n        simp_all [Finset.image_image, Function.LeftInverse]\n        <;>\n        aesop\n      }) <;>\n      aesop\n    simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n    <;>\n    aesop\n  have h_image_card : (p.snd.edgeSet).toFinset.card = ( (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet.image s ).toFinset.card := by\n    rw [h_card_eq]\n  have h_card_finset : (p.snd.edgeSet).card = (p.snd.edgeSet).toFinset.card := by\n    simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n  have h_card_finset_image : ( (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet.image s ).toFinset.card = ( (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet ).toFinset.card := by\n    simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n    <;>\n    simp_all [Finset.card_image_of_injective]\n    <;>\n    aesop\n  simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n  <;>\n  try {\n    simp_all [Finset.card_image_of_injective]\n    <;>\n    aesop\n  }\n  <;>\n  try {\n    simp_all [Equiv.Perm.apply_symm_apply]\n    <;>\n    aesop\n  }\n  <;>\n  try {\n    aesop\n  }",
      "\n  obtain ⟨ s, hs⟩ := heq\n  rw [hs]\n  have h_card_eq : (p.snd.edges.toFinset).image (fun e => (⟨(s e.1 : ℕ), by\n    fin_cases e.1 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n    ⟩, ⟨(s e.2 : ℕ), by\n    fin_cases e.2 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n    ⟩)) =\n    (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset := by\n    -- Prove that the edges of the permuted walk are the image of the edges of the original walk under s.\n    have h_edges_eq : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges =\n      (p.snd.edges.map fun e => (⟨(s e.1 : ℕ), by\n        fin_cases e.1 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n        ⟩, ⟨(s e.2 : ℕ), by\n        fin_cases e.2 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n        ⟩)) := by\n      -- Use the fact that permMapWalk maps each edge to its image under s.\n      have h_edges_permutation : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p).edges =\n        (p.edges.map fun e => (⟨(s e.1 : ℕ), by\n          fin_cases e.1 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n          ⟩, ⟨(s e.2 : ℕ), by\n          fin_cases e.2 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n          ⟩)) := by\n        intros u v p\n        induction' p with u v w h p ih\n        · simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk, List.map]\n        · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk, List.map]\n          <;> aesop\n        · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk, List.map]\n          <;> aesop\n      exact h_edges_permutation _ _ _\n    rw [h_edges_eq]\n    -- Use the fact that the image of a set under a function is the same as the image of the finset.\n    simp [List.toFinset_map]\n    <;> aesop\n  rw [← h_card_eq]\n  -- Use the fact that the cardinality of the image of a set under an injective function is the same as the cardinality of the set.\n  have h_injective : Function.Injective (fun e : Fin2 (Fin n) => (⟨(s e.1 : ℕ), by\n    fin_cases e.1 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n    ⟩, ⟨(s e.2 : ℕ), by\n    fin_cases e.2 <;> fin_cases s <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]\n    ⟩)) := by\n    intro ⟨a₁, a₂⟩ ⟨b₁, b₂⟩ h\n    simp_all [Fin.ext_iff]\n    <;>\n    (try cases a₁ <;> cases a₂ <;> cases b₁ <;> cases b₂ <;> simp_all [Fin.ext_iff]) <;>\n    (try omega) <;>\n    (try simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_symm]) <;>\n    (try aesop)\n  simp [Finset.card_image_of_injective h_injective]",
      "\n  obtain ⟨ s, hs ⟩ := heq;\n  rw [hs];\n  -- Since these two sets are equal, their cardinalities are equal.\n  have h_card_eq : (p.snd.edgeSet).image s = (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet := by\n    -- By definition of `permMapWalk`, the edge set of the permuted walk is the image of the edge set of the original walk under `s`.\n    have h_edge_eq : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges = List.map (fun e => e) p.snd.edges := by\n      have h_edge_eq : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p).edges = List.map (fun e => e) p.edges := by\n        intros u v p\n        induction' p with u v w h p ih\n        · rfl\n        · -- By definition of `permMapWalk`, the edges of the permuted walk are the edges of the original walk.\n          simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges]\n          <;> aesop\n        · -- By definition of `edges`, the edges of a loop walk are the same as the edges of the underlying walk.\n          simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, List.map]\n          <;> aesop\n      exact h_edge_eq _ _ _\n    unfold SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet at *\n    <;> simp_all [Finset.image_eq_map, Finset.map_map]\n  rw [ ← h_card_eq, Finset.card_image_of_injective _ s.injective ]",
      "\n  have h_main : (edgeSet p.2).card = (edgeSet q.2).card := by\n    obtain ⟨s, hs⟩ := heq\n    rw [hs]\n    have h_card_eq : (p.snd.edges.toFinset).card = ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset).card := by\n      have h_bij : ∀ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)), e ∈ (p.snd.edges.toFinset) ↔ (s e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset) := by\n        intro e\n        have h₁ : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (s e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) ↔ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) := by\n          intro u v p\n          induction' p with u v p ih generalizing e\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, LoopWalk.nil]\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.darts, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.darts, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n        have h₂ : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (s e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) ↔ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) := by\n          intro u v p\n          induction' p with u v p ih generalizing e\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, LoopWalk.nil]\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.darts, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.darts, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n        have h₃ : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (s e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) ↔ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) := by\n          intro u v p\n          induction' p with u v p ih generalizing e\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, LoopWalk.nil]\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.darts, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.darts, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n        have h₄ : (s e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset) ↔ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.snd.edges.toFinset) := by\n          have h₅ : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (s e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p).edges.toFinset) ↔ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)) ∈ (p.edges.toFinset) := by\n            intro u v p\n            induction' p with u v p ih generalizing e\n            · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, LoopWalk.nil, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMap, Sym2.ext_iff]\n            · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMap, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n              <;> aesop\n            · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMap, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n              <;> aesop\n          have h₆ := h₅ p.1 p.2 p.snd\n          simp_all\n          <;> aesop\n        simp_all\n        <;> aesop\n      have h₁ : (p.snd.edges.toFinset).card = ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset).card := by\n        have h₂ : (p.snd.edges.toFinset).card = ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset).card := by\n          -- Use the fact that the bijection preserves the cardinality of the edge set\n          have h₃ : ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset) = (p.snd.edges.toFinset).image (fun e : Sym2 (Fin n) => s e) := by\n            -- Prove that the edge set of the permuted walk is the image of the edge set of the original walk under the permutation\n            have h₄ : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p).edges.toFinset) = (p.edges.toFinset).image (fun e : Sym2 (Fin n) => s e) := by\n              intro u v p\n              induction' p with u v p ih generalizing\n              · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, LoopWalk.nil, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMap, Sym2.ext_iff]\n              · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMap, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n                <;> aesop\n              · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMap, Finset.mem_coe, Sym2.ext_iff]\n                <;> aesop\n            have h₅ := h₄ p.1 p.2 p.snd\n            simp_all\n          rw [h₃]\n          -- The image of a finite set under a bijection has the same cardinality as the original set\n          have h₆ : ((p.snd.edges.toFinset).image (fun e : Sym2 (Fin n) => s e)).card = (p.snd.edges.toFinset).card := by\n            -- Since s is a permutation, it is bijective, and the cardinality is preserved\n            apply Finset.card_image_of_injective\n            intro x y h\n            simp_all [Equiv.injective]\n          rw [h₆]\n        exact h₂\n      exact h₁\n    have h₂ : (p.snd.edges.toFinset).card = (edgeSet p.2).card := by\n      simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n      <;> rfl\n    have h₃ : ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset).card = (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)).card := by\n      simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n      <;> rfl\n    have h₄ : (edgeSet p.2).card = (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)).card := by\n      calc\n        (edgeSet p.2).card = (p.snd.edges.toFinset).card := by rw [h₂]\n        _ = ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edges.toFinset).card := by rw [h_card_eq]\n        _ = (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)).card := by rw [h₃]\n    rw [h₄]\n  exact h_main",
      "",
      "rfl",
      "\n  have h_main : (edgeSet p.2).card = (edgeSet q.2).card := by\n    obtain ⟨s, hs⟩ := heq\n    rw [hs]\n    have h_edge_eq : (edgeSet p.snd).image (fun e => SetLike.coe (-e-)) = (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.snd).edgeSet := by\n      simp [K, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.map, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges,\n        Finset.image]\n      <;>\n      (try decide) <;>\n      (try ring_nf) <;>\n      (try simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.map, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, Finset.image]) <;>\n      (try omega) <;>\n      (try aesop)\n      <;>\n      (try ext e <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n      <;>\n      (try ring_nf at * <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n      <;>\n      (try omega)\n      <;>\n      (try aesop)\n      <;>\n      (try simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n      <;>\n      (try ring_nf at * <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n      <;>\n      (try omega)\n      <;>\n      (try aesop)\n    rw [← h_edge_eq]\n    <;> simp [Finset.card_image_of_injective, Function.Injective]\n    <;>\n    (try decide) <;>\n    (try ring_nf) <;>\n    (try simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.map, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, Finset.image]) <;>\n    (try omega) <;>\n    (try aesop)\n    <;>\n    (try ext e <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n    <;>\n    (try ring_nf at * <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n    <;>\n    (try omega)\n    <;>\n    (try aesop)\n    <;>\n    (try simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n    <;>\n    (try ring_nf at * <;> simp_all [Equiv.Perm.sign_mul, Equiv.Perm.sign_inv, mul_inv_cancel_right])\n    <;>\n    (try omega)\n    <;>\n    (try aesop)\n  \n  exact h_main",
      "\n  obtain ⟨s, hs⟩ := heq\n  rw [hs]\n  -- Use the fact that the edges are mapped bijectively under permutation\n  have h_edges_perm : (edgeSet p.2).image s = (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)) := by\n    have h_edges : ∀ {u v : Fin n} (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p)).toFinset = (edgeSet p).toFinset.image s := by\n      intros u v p\n      have h_darts : ∀ {u v : Fin n} (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (permMapWalk n s p).dartSet = (p.dartSet).image s := by\n        intro u v p\n        induction' p with u v w h p ih\n        · simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.dartSet, permMapWalk_nil]\n        · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.dartSet, permMapWalk_cons, Set.image_insert, Set.image_singleton]\n          <;>\n          (try aesop) <;>\n          (try simp_all [Sym2.mk_injEq, Equiv.Perm.inv_def]) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n        · simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.dartSet, permMapWalk_loop, Set.image_insert, Set.image_singleton]\n          <;>\n          (try aesop) <;>\n          (try simp_all [Sym2.mk_injEq, Equiv.Perm.inv_def]) <;>\n          (try aesop)\n      have h_edges : ∀ {u v : Fin n} (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (permMapWalk n s p).edgeSet.toFinset = (p.edgeSet.toFinset).image s := by\n        intro u v p\n        have h₁ : (permMapWalk n s p).edgeSet.toFinset = (permMapWalk n s p).edges.toFinset := by\n          simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n        have h₂ : p.edgeSet.toFinset = p.edges.toFinset := by\n          simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n        have h₃ : ∀ {u v : Fin n} (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (permMapWalk n s p).edges.toFinset = (p.edges.toFinset).image s := by\n          intro u v p\n          have h₄ : ∀ {u v : Fin n} (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (permMapWalk n s p).edges.toFinset = (p.edges.toFinset).image s := by\n            intro u v p\n            induction' p with u v w h p ih\n            · simp [permMapWalk_nil, edges]\n            · simp_all [permMapWalk_cons, edges, Finset.image_insert]\n              <;>\n              (try aesop) <;>\n              (try\n                {\n                  simp_all [Sym2.mem_swap, Sym2.map, s.map]\n                  <;>\n                  aesop\n                })\n              <;>\n              (try\n                {\n                  simp_all [Finset.mem_image]\n                  <;>\n                  aesop\n                })\n            · simp_all [permMapWalk_loop, edges, Finset.image_insert]\n              <;>\n              (try aesop) <;>\n              (try\n                {\n                  simp_all [Sym2.mem_swap, Sym2.map, s.map]\n                  <;>\n                  aesop\n                })\n              <;>\n              (try\n                {\n                  simp_all [Finset.mem_image]\n                  <;>\n                  aesop\n                })\n          exact h₄ p\n        simp_all [h₁, h₂]\n        <;>\n        aesop\n      exact h_edges p\n    have h₁ : (permMapWalk n s p.2).edgeSet.toFinset = (p.2.edgeSet.toFinset).image s := h_edges p.2\n    simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n    <;>\n    aesop\n  have h_card_eq : (p.2.edges.toFinset).card = (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset.card := by\n    have h_card : (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset.card = (p.2.edges.toFinset).card := by\n      have h_image : (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset = (p.2.edges.toFinset).image s := by\n        have h_darts : ∀ {u v : Fin n} (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (permMapWalk n s p).edges.toFinset = (p.edges.toFinset).image s := by\n          intro u v p\n          induction' p with u v w h p ih\n          · simp [permMapWalk_nil, edges]\n          · simp_all [permMapWalk_cons, edges, Finset.image_insert]\n            <;>\n            (try aesop) <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                simp_all [Sym2.mem_swap, Sym2.map, s.map]\n                <;>\n                aesop\n              })\n            <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                simp_all [Finset.mem_image]\n                <;>\n                aesop\n              })\n          · simp_all [permMapWalk_loop, edges, Finset.image_insert]\n            <;>\n            (try aesop) <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                simp_all [Sym2.mem_swap, Sym2.map, s.map]\n                <;>\n                aesop\n              })\n            <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                simp_all [Finset.mem_image]\n                <;>\n                aesop\n              })\n        exact h_darts p.2\n      rw [h_image]\n      rw [Finset.card_image_of_injective]\n      <;> simp [s.injective]\n    linarith\n  simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n  <;>\n  aesop",
      "\n  have h_main : (edgeSet p.2).card = (edgeSet q.2).card := by\n    obtain ⟨s, hq⟩ := heq\n    rw [hq]\n    have h_card_eq : (p.2.edges.toFinset.image s).card = (p.2.edges.toFinset.image s).card := rfl\n    have h_image : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2).edges = p.2.edges.map (Graph.Bijective.map_adj (fun x y => (s • x, s • y))) := by\n      induction p.2 with\n      | nil => rfl\n      | cons u v p ih =>\n        simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, Dart.map]\n        <;>\n        (try simp_all [Dart.map, Bij.map_rel]) <;>\n        (try norm_num) <;>\n        (try aesop)\n      | loop u p => simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, Dart.map]\n        <;>\n        (try simp_all [Dart.map, Bij.map_rel]) <;>\n        (try norm_num) <;>\n        (try aesop)\n    have h_bijection : (p.2.edges.toFinset.image s).card = (p.2.edges.toFinset).card := by\n      have h1 : (p.2.edges.toFinset.image s).card = (p.2.edges.toFinset.card) := by\n        apply Finset.card_image_of_injective\n        intro x y hxy\n        simp_all [Function.Embedding]\n        <;>\n        aesop\n      linarith\n    have h_final : (edgeSet (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2)).card = (edgeSet p.2).card := by\n      calc\n        (edgeSet (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2)).card =\n            ((SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset).card := by rfl\n        _ = (p.2.edges.toFinset.image s).card := by\n          have h2 : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset = p.2.edges.toFinset.image s := by\n            have h3 : (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2).edges = List.map (fun d => (s • d.1, s • d.2)) p.2.edges := by\n              induction p.2 with\n              | nil => rfl\n              | cons u v p ih =>\n                simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, Dart.map]\n                <;>\n                (try simp_all [Dart.map, Bij.map_rel]) <;>\n                (try norm_num) <;>\n                (try aesop)\n              | loop u p =>\n                simp_all [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, Dart.map]\n                <;>\n                (try simp_all [Dart.map, Bij.map_rel]) <;>\n                (try norm_num) <;>\n                (try aesop)\n            calc\n              (SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset =\n                  (List.map (fun d => (s • d.1, s • d.2)) p.2.edges).toFinset := by rw [h3]\n              _ = p.2.edges.toFinset.image s := by\n                simp [List.toFinset_map]\n                <;>\n                congr 1 <;>\n                ext <;>\n                simp [Prod.ext_iff]\n                <;>\n                aesop\n          rw [h2]\n          <;>\n          simp [edgeSet]\n          <;>\n          aesop\n        _ = (p.2.edges.toFinset).card := by\n          have h2 : (p.2.edges.toFinset.image s).card = (p.2.edges.toFinset.card) := by\n            apply Finset.card_image_of_injective\n            intro x y hxy\n            simp_all [Function.Embedding]\n            <;>\n            aesop\n          linarith\n        _ = (edgeSet p.2).card := by rfl\n    simp_all [edgeSet]\n    <;>\n    aesop\n  exact h_main",
      "\n  have h_main : ∃ (s : Equiv.Perm (Fin n)), q = ⟨s p.1, permMapWalk n s p.2⟩ := by\n    obtain ⟨s, hs⟩ := heq\n    refine' ⟨s, _⟩\n    simpa [hs] using hs\n  \n  have h_image_eq : ∀ (s : Equiv.Perm (Fin n)), (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)).card = (edgeSet p.2).card := by\n    intro s\n    have h₁ : ∀ (u v : Fin n) (p : (K n).LoopWalk u v), (permMapWalk n s p).edgeSet.card = p.edgeSet.card := by\n      intro u v p\n      induction' p with u v p ih\n      · simp [permMapWalk]\n      · simp_all [permMapWalk, permMap, EdgeSet, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet, Finset.card_union_add_card_inter]\n        <;>\n        (try simp_all [Finset.card_singleton, Finset.card_insert_of_not_mem, Finset.mem_singleton]) <;>\n        (try simp_all [Finset.card_union_add_card_inter]) <;>\n        (try omega) <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            aesop\n          })\n      · simp_all [permMapWalk, permMap, EdgeSet, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet, Finset.card_union_add_card_inter]\n        <;>\n        (try simp_all [Finset.card_singleton, Finset.card_insert_of_not_mem, Finset.mem_singleton]) <;>\n        (try simp_all [Finset.card_union_add_card_inter]) <;>\n        (try omega) <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            aesop\n          })\n    have h₂ := h₁ p.1 p.1 p.2\n    simpa [EdgeSet] using h₂\n  \n  have h_final : (edgeSet p.2).card = (edgeSet q.2).card := by\n    obtain ⟨s, hs⟩ := h_main\n    have h₁ : q.2 = permMapWalk n s p.2 := by\n      simp [hs] at *\n      <;> rfl\n    rw [h₁]\n    have h₂ : (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)).card = (edgeSet p.2).card := h_image_eq s\n    linarith\n  \n  apply h_final",
      "\n  obtain ⟨s, rfl⟩ := heq\n  have h_map_perm : (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)).card = (edgeSet p.2).card := by\n    have h_edge_map_eq : (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)) = (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e : Σ (x y : Fin n), (x, y) => (↑s x, ↑s y)) := by\n      induction p.2 with\n      | nil =>\n        simp [SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet, SetLike.ext_iff]\n      | @cons u v _ h p ih =>\n        simp_all [SimpleGraph.Loopwalk.Dart, LoopWalk.permMap, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSetSet]\n        <;>\n        (try aesop) :\n        <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            simp_all [Sym2.ext_iff, Finset.ext_iff]\n            <;>\n            (try\n {\n              aesop\n            })\n            <;>\n              (try\n {\n                intros <;> simp_all [Function.Injective] <;> aesop\n              })\n          })\n        <;>\n        (try\n {\n          simp_all [Finset.ext_iff]\n          <;>\n            (try\n {\n              aesop\n            })\n          <;>\n            (try\n {\n              intros <;> simp_all [Function.Injective] <;> aesop\n            })\n        })\n      | @Loop u v p ih =>\n        simp_all [LoopWalk.permMap, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edgeSet]\n        <;>\n        (try aesop)\n        <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            simp_all [Sym2.ext_iff, Finset.ext_iff]\n            <;>\n            (try\n {\n              aesop\n            })\n            <;>\n            (try\n {\n              intros <;> simp_all [Function.Injective] <;> aesop\n            })\n          })\n        <;>\n        (try\n {\n          simp_all [Finset.ext_iff]\n          <;>\n            (try\n {\n              aesop\n            })\n          <;>\n            (try\n {\n              intros <;> simp_all [Function.Injective] <;> aesop\n            })\n        })\n    have h_image_card : (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e : Σ (x y : Fin n), (x, y) => (↑s x, ↑s y)).card = (edgeSet p.2).card := by\n      have h_inj : Function.Injective (fun e : Σ (x y : Fin n), (x, y) => (↑s x, ↑s y)) := by\n        intro ⟨x₁, y₁⟩ ⟨x₂, y₂⟩ h\n        simp_all [Fin.ext_iff]\n        <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            simp_all [Equiv.Perm.apply_injective]\n          })\n      rw [Finset.card_image_of_injective _ h_inj]\n    rw [h_edge_map_eq, h_image_card]\n  rw [h_map_perm]",
      "\n  obtain ⟨s, hs⟩ := heq\n  rw [hs]\n  have h_image : (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) = edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2) := by\n    have h_image : ∀ (e : Sym2 (Fin n)), e ∈ edgeSet p.2 → SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e ∈ (edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2)) := by\n      intro e he\n      have h₁ : e ∈ edgeSet p.2 := he\n      have h₂ : e ∈ p.2.edges.toFinset := by\n        simp_all [edgeSet]\n      have h₃ : e ∈ p.2.edges := by\n        simpa [Finset.mem_coe] using h₂\n      have h₄ : (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) ∈ (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges := by\n        have h₅ : (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) ∈ (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges := by\n          simp [permMap, permMapWalk, SimpleGraph.mapSym, edgeSet, K, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, List.map_map] at h₃ ⊢\n          <;>\n          (try {\n            cases p.2 <;> simp_all [SimpleGraph.Adj, Sym2.eq_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          }) <;>\n          (try {\n            simp_all [SimpleGraph.Adj, Sym2.eq_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          })\n        exact h₅\n      have h₆ : (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) ∈ (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset := by\n        simpa [Finset.mem_coe] using h₄\n      simp_all [edgeSet]\n    have h_subset : (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) ⊆ edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2) := by\n      intro e he\n      rcases Finset.mem_image.mp he with ⟨e', he'_in, rfl⟩\n      have h := h_image e' he'_in\n      simpa [edgeSet] using h\n    have h_card_image : (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) = edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2) := by\n      have h_subset₁ : (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) ⊆ edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2) := h_subset\n      have h_subset₂ : edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2) ⊆ (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) := by\n        intro e he\n        have h₁ : e ∈ edgeSet (permMapWalk n s p.2) := he\n        have h₂ : e ∈ (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges.toFinset := by\n          simp_all [edgeSet]\n        have h₃ : e ∈ (permMapWalk n s p.2).edges := by\n          simpa [Finset.mem_coe] using h₂\n        have h₄ : (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e) ∈ (p.2.edges.toFinset) := by\n          simp [permMap, permMapWalk, SimpleGraph.mapSym, K, SimpleGraph.LoopWalk.edges, List.map_map] at h₃ ⊢\n          <;>\n          (try {\n            cases p.2 <;> simp_all [SimpleGraph.Adj, Sym2.eq_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          }) <;>\n          (try {\n            simp_all [SimpleGraph.Adj, Sym2.eq_iff]\n            <;> aesop\n          })\n        have h₅ : (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e) ∈ (edgeSet p.2) := by\n          simp_all [edgeSet]\n        have h₆ : e = (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) ((SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e))) := by\n          have h₇ : SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) ((SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e)) = e := by\n            simp [Equiv.Symm.apply_symm_apply]\n          rw [h₇]\n        have h₇ : (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e) ∈ (edgeSet p.2) := h₅\n        have h₈ : e = (SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) ((SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e))):= by\n          have h₉ : SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) ((SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e)) = e := by\n            simp [Equiv.Symm.apply_symm_apply]\n          rw [h₉]\n        have h₉ : e ∈ (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s) e) := by\n          rw [Finset.mem_image]\n          refine' ⟨(SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap n s)⁻¹ e), _⟩\n          <;> simp_all [h₈]\n          <;>\n          (try {\n            aesop\n          })\n        simp_all [h₈]\n      exact Finset.Subset.antisymm h_subset₁ h_subset₂\n    exact h_card_image\n  have h_card_image : (edgeSet p.2).card = (edgeSet p.2).image (fun e => SimpleGraph.mapSym (K n) (permMap